obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (39487)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes `1 18th April, 1957, vide notification No. S.R.O. 88, dated 7th January, 1957, see Gazette of India, Part II, sec. 3.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665&sectionId=39487&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Manipur`
  line `(Village Authorities in Hill Areas) Act, 1956.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of the hill areas of the Union territory of Manipur.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (39488)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665&sectionId=39488&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,—`
  line
  line `(a) "Chief Commissioner" means the Chief Commissioner of Manipur;`
  line
  line `(b) "Deputy Commissioner" means the Deputy Commissioner of Manipur and includes the`
  line `Additional Deputy commissioner thereof;`
  line
  line `(c) "heinous offence" means—`
  line
  line `(i) any of the following offences punishable under the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860), that is`
  line `to say, any offence under Chapter VI, rioting, any offence under Chapter XII, murder,`
  line `culpable homicide not amounting to murder, grievous hurt, kidnapping or abducting in order to`
  line `subject a person to slavery, buying or disposing of any person as a slave, habitual dealing in`
  line `slaves, rape, robbery, dacoity, mischief by fire or explosive substance, and house breaking;`
  line
  line `(ii) any offence punishable under the Indian Arms Act, 1878 (11 of 1878);`
  line
  line `and includes any attempt, preparation or conspiracy to commit, and abetment of, any of the offences`
  line `specified in sub-clause (i) or sub-clause (ii);`
  line
  line `(d) "hill areas" mean such areas in the Hill tracts of the Union territory of Manipur as the Chief`
  line `Commissioner may, by notification in the Official Gazette, declare to be hill areas;`
  line
  line `(e) "legal practitioner" includes a pleader, mukhtar or revenue-agent;`
  line
  line `(f) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (39489)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Constitution of Village Authorities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665&sectionId=39489&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) For every village having twenty or more tax-paying houses`
  line `there shall be a village Authority consisting of`
  line
  line `(a) five members, where the number of tax-paying houses in the village is not less than twenty`
  line `but is not more than sixty;`
  line
  line `(b) seven members, where the number of tax-paying houses in the village is more than sixty but is`
  line `not more than one hundred;`
  line
  line `(c) ten members, where the number of tax-paying houses in the village is more than one hundred`
  line `but is not more than one hundred and fifty;`
  line
  line `(d) twelve members, where the number of tax-paying houses in the village is more than one`
  line `hundred and fifty.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chief Commissioner may, having regard to the general interests of the people of any`
  line `village as also to the demand, if any, from the people of that village for an elected Village Authority,`
  line `declare, by notification in the Official Gazette, that the village shall have an elected Village Authority,`
  line `and thereupon the members of the Village Authority of that village shall be elected in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of this Act and the rules made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(3) Where no declaration under sub-section (2) has been made in relation to any village the members`
  line `of the Village Authority of that village shall be nominated by the Chief Commissioner.`
  line
  line `(4) Where there is a Chief Khulakpa in a village, he shall be the ex officio chairman of the`
  line `Village Authority of that village; and where there is no such Chief or Khulakpa in the village, the`
  line `chairman of the village Authority of that village shall be elected by the members of the Village Authority`
  line `from among themselves.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (39490)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Qualifications for membership of Village Authorities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665&sectionId=39490&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `A person shall not be qualified to be`
  line `chosen as a member of a Village Authority unless he—`
  line
  line `(a) is a citizen of India;`
  line
  line `(b) is not less than twenty-five years of age; and`
  line
  line `(c) in the case of membership of an elected Village Authority, is registered in the electoral roll as`
  line `a voter for the election of a member of the Village Authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (39491)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Disqualifications for membership of Village Authorities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665&sectionId=39491&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `A person shall be disqualified for`
  line `being chosen as, and for being, a member of a Village Authority,—`
  line
  line `(a) if he is a member of any other Village Authority;`
  line
  line `(b) if he is of unsound mind and stands so declared by a competent authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (39492)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Term of office of members of Village Authorities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665&sectionId=39492&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `The term of office of members of a Village`
  line `Authority shall be three years from the date appointed for its first meeting.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (39493)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Election of members of Village Authorities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665&sectionId=39493&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `The election of members of the Village Authority`
  line `of a village shall be on the basis of adult suffrage, that is to say, every person who is a citizen of India and`
  line `who is ordinarily resident in the village and is not less than twenty-one years of age on such date as may`
  line `be fixed by rules made under this Act, shall be entitled to be registered as a voter at any such election.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—A person shall be deemed to be ordinarily resident in a village if he ordinarily resides`
  line `in that village or owns, or is in possession of, a dwelling house therein.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (39494)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Power to remove members of Village Authorities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665&sectionId=39494&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Deputy Commissioner may remove`
  line `any member of a Village Authority from his office—`
  line
  line `(a) who is convicted of any non-bailable offence; or`
  line
  line `(b) who refuses to act, or becomes incapable of acting, or is declared to be insolvent; or`
  line
  line `(c) who has been declared by notification to be disqualified for employment in the public service;`
  line or
  line
  line `(d) who, without an excuse sufficient in the opinion of the Deputy Commissioner, absents himself`
  line `from six consecutive meetings of the Village Authority; or`
  line
  line `(e) who has been guilty of misconduct in the discharge of his duties, or of any disgraceful`
  line `conduct, if two-thirds of the total number of the members of the Village Authority at a meeting`
  line `recommend his removal.`
  line
  line `(2) No person who has been removed from his office under clause (a) or clause (c) of sub-section (1)`
  line `shall be eligible for re-nomination or re-election except with the previous permission of the Chief`
  line `Commissioner obtained by such person in the prescribed manner.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (39495)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Resignation of members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665&sectionId=39495&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `A member of a Village Authority may resign his office by writing`
  line `under his hand addressed to the chairman of the Authority but shall continue in office until his`
  line `resignation has been accepted in a meeting of the Authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (39496)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Filling of causal vacancies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665&sectionId=39496&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `When the office of a member of a Village Authority becomes`
  line `vacant by his removal, resignation or death, a new member shall be nominated or elected to fill the`
  line `vacancy and shall hold office so long as the member whose place he fills would have been entitled to`
  line `hold office if such vacancy had not occurred.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (39497)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Bar to interference by courts in election matters.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665&sectionId=39497&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `No election of a member of a Village`
  line `Authority shall be called in question in any court, and no court shall grant an injunction,—`
  line
  line `(a) to postpone the election of a member of a Village Authority; or`
  line
  line `(b) to prohibit a person, declared to have been duly elected under this Act, from taking part in the`
  line `proceedings of a Village Authority of which he has been elected a member; of`
  line
  line `(c) to prohibit members nominated or elected for a Village Authority from entering upon their`
  line duties.
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (39498)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Election disputes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665&sectionId=39498&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) If a dispute arises as to the election of any member of a Village`
  line `Authority, the matter shall be referred to the Deputy Commissioner who shall decide the same after`
  line `giving notice to the parties concerned and after taking such evidence as may be produced.`
  line
  line `(2) The order of the Deputy Commissioner may, within thirty days from the date thereof, be revised`
  line `by the Chief Commissioner whose decision shall be final and shall not be questioned in any court.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (39499)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Validation of acts and proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665&sectionId=39499&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `No Act done or proceedings taken by a Village`
  line `Authority under this Act shall be questioned on the ground merely of—`
  line
  line `(a) the existence of any vacancy in, or any defect in the constitution of, the Village Authority;`
  line
  line `(b) any defect or irregularity not affecting the merits of the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (39500)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Incorporation of Village Authorities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665&sectionId=39500&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `Every Village Authority shall be a body corporate by the`
  line `name of the village for which it is constituted and shall have perpetual succession and a common seal, and`
  line `shall by the said name sue and be sued, with power to acquire, hold and dispose of property, both`
  line `movable and immovable, and to contract and do all other things necessary for the purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (39501)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Control of Village Authorities by sub-divisional magistrate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665&sectionId=39501&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the general`
  line `superintendence and control of the Deputy commissioner, the sub-divisional magistrate shall have control`
  line `over all the Village Authorities within the local limits of his jurisdiction.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (39502)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Functions of Village Authorities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665&sectionId=39502&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Village Authority constituted under this Act shall,`
  line `within the local limits of its jurisdiction, perform the following functions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) it shall, to the best of its ability maintain law and order and for there purpose exercise and`
  line `perform the powers and duties generally conferred and imposed on the police by or under the Police`
  line `Act, 1861 (5 of 1861):`
  line
  line `Provided that a Village Authority shall not be deemed to be a police officer within the meaning of`
  line `sections 25 and 16 of the Indian Evidence Act, 1872 (1 of 1872), or section 162 of the Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898);`
  line
  line `(b) it shall cause to be arrested without any order from a magistrate and without a warrant--`
  line
  line `(i) any person who is a vagrant or commits a heinous offence or who has been concerned in`
  line `any such offence or against whom a reasonable complaint has been made or credible information`
  line `has been received or a reasonable suspicion exists of his having been so concerned,`
  line
  line `(ii) any person against whom a hue and cry has been raised on the ground of his having been`
  line `concerned in any heinous offence, whether such offence has been or is being committed within its`
  line `jurisdiction or outside it,`
  line
  line `(iii) any person for whose arrest a requisition has been received from a police officer;`
  line `provided that the requisition specifies the person to be arrested and the offence or other cause for`
  line `which the arrest is to be made or it appears therefrom that the person might lawfully be arrested`
  line `without a warrant by the officer who issued the requisition,`
  line
  line `(iv) any person designing to commit any heinous offence of which the Village Authority has`
  line `knowledge, if the commission of offence cannot otherwise be prevented,`
  line
  line `(v) any person who obstructs the Village Authority in the performance of its functions under`
  line `this Act or rules made thereunder or a police officer while in the execution of his duty, and`
  line
  line `(vi) any person who has escaped, or attempts to escape, from lawful custody:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a Village Authority is unable to arrest an offender it shall forthwith`
  line `report the matter to the sub-divisional magistrate who shall provide the Village Authority with`
  line `such assistance as it requires:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Village Authority may pursue beyond the local limits of its`
  line `jurisdiction any person who has committed a heinous offence or is a vagrant or of bad or`
  line `suspicious character, and arrest such person outside the local limits of its jurisdiction with the`
  line `consent of the Village Authority within the local limits of whose jurisdiction the person pursued`
  line `is found;`
  line
  line `(c) it shall give immediate information to the sub-divisional magistrate of every unnatural,`
  line `suspicious or sudden death which may occur, and of any heinous offence which may be committed,`
  line `within the local limits of its jurisdiction and shall keep the sub-divisional magistrate informed of all`
  line `disputes which are likely to lead to a riot or serious affray; and`
  line
  line `(d) it shall supply any information which any police officer or the sub-divisional magistrate or`
  line `the Deputy commissioner may require from it.`
  line
  line `(2) No person who is arrested under this section shall be detained in custody without being informed,`
  line `as soon as may be, of the grounds of such arrest.`
  line
  line `(3) Every person who is arrested and detained in custody shall be produced before the nearest`
  line `magistrate within a period of twenty four hours of such arrest excluding the time necessary for the`
  line `journey from the place of arrest to the court of the magistrate and no such person shall be detained in`
  line `custody beyond the said period without the authority of a magistrate.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (39503)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Obligation to assist Village Authorities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665&sectionId=39503&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person shall be bound to render, to a`
  line `Village Authority performing the functions under this Act, all the assistance which he is bound to render`
  line `to a police officer under section 42 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898), and every`
  line `person who refuses or neglects to comply with any requisition for such assistance shall be punishable`
  line `with fine may extend to—`
  line
  line `(a) two hundred rupees, where the sentence passed by a Village court; or`
  line
  line `(b) five hundred rupees, where the sentence is passed by the court of a sub-divisional magistrate.`
  line
  line `(2) Against an order passed under sub-section (1) an appeal shall lie—`
  line
  line `(a) to the court of sub-divisional magistrate, where the order is passed by a village court;`
  line
  line `(b) to the court of session, where the order is passed by the court of the`
  line `sub-divisional magistrate,`
  line
  line `within period of thirty days from the date of such order or within such longer period as the appellate court`
  line `may allow:`
  line
  line `Provided that no appeal shall lie in any case in which a village court passes a sentence of fine not`
  line `exceeding twenty rupees or in any case in which the court of a sub-divisional magistrate passes a sentence`
  line `of fine not exceeding one hundred rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (39544)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Power of Chief Commissioner to call for records of Village Authorities, sub-divisional magistrate or Deputy Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665&sectionId=39544&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `The Chief Commissioner may at any time call for and examine`
  line `the record of any proceeding before a Village Authority, village court, sub-divisional magistrate or`
  line `Deputy Commissioner under section 17 for the purpose of satisfying himself as to the correctness, legality`
  line `or propriety of any finding, sentence or order recorded or passed and after perusing the record set aside,`
  line `modify or confirm such finding, sentence or order:`
  line
  line `Provided that where an order has been made by the court of session in an appeal preferred under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 17, the Chief Commissioner shall not interfere with such appellate order.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (39505)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Constitution of village courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665&sectionId=39505&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `Whenever a Village Authority has been constituted for any`
  line `village, the Chief Commissioner may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint any two or more of`
  line `the members of the Village Authority to be a village court during their term of office as members of the`
  line `Village Authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (39506)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Jurisdiction of village courts in criminal cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665&sectionId=39506&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the`
  line `Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898), the village court shall have jurisdiction concurrent with`
  line `that of the criminal court within the local limits of whose jurisdiction the village is situated for the trial of`
  line `all offences specified in the Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (39507)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `How cases may be instituted.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665&sectionId=39507&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) A case before a village court may be instituted by a`
  line `complaint, made orally or in writing, to a member of the village court.`
  line
  line `(2) If the complaint is made orally, the member shall record the name of the complainant, the name of`
  line `the person against whom the complaint is made, the nature of the offence and such other particulars, if`
  line `any, as may be, prescribed, and shall direct the complainant to appear before the village court.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (39508)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Power of village courts to dismiss or refuse to entertain complaint.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665&sectionId=39508&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) If upon the fact of the`
  line `complaint, or on examining the complaint, the village court is of opinion that the complaint is frivolous`
  line `vexatious or untrue, it shall dismiss the case by order in writing.`
  line
  line `(2) If at any time it appears to the village court—`
  line
  line `(a) that it has no jurisdiction to cry the case, or`
  line
  line `(b) that the offence is one for which the sentence which the court is competent to pass would be`
  line `inadequate, or`
  line
  line `(c) that the case is one which should not be tried by the court,`
  line
  line `it shall direct the complainant to the proper court.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (39509)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Dismissal of case for default.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665&sectionId=39509&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `If in any case before a village court the complainant fails to`
  line `appear on the day fixed, or if in the opinion of the court he shows negligence in prosecuting his case, the`
  line `court may dismiss the case for default, and such order of dismissal shall operate as an acquittal.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (39510)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Proceedings preliminary to trial.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665&sectionId=39510&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the complaint is not dismissed, the village court shall,`
  line `subject to the provisions of section 53, by summons or otherwise require the accused to appear and`
  line `answer the complaint.`
  line
  line `(2) If the accused fails to appear or cannot be found, the court shall report the fact to the nearest`
  line `magistrate, who may issue a warrant for the arrest of the accused and when arrested may forward him for`
  line `trial to the village court or release him on bail to appear before it.`
  line
  line `(3) The village court shall, if possible, try the case on the day on which the accused appears or is`
  line `brought before it; but if that is not possible, the village court shall release him on his executing a bond for`
  line `a sum not exceeding two hundred rupees to appear before the court on any subsequent day to which the`
  line `trial may be adjourned.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (39511)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Bar to appeal from the order of village courts, but power to order retrial.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665&sectionId=39511&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line Notwithstanding
  line `anything contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898), there shall be no appeal by a`
  line `convicted person in any case tried by a village court:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Deputy Commissioner or the sub-divisional magistrate, if satisfied that a failure of`
  line `justice has occurred, may, of his own motion or on the application of the parties concerned, cancel or`
  line `modify any order of conviction or of compensation made by a village court or direct the retrial of any`
  line `case by a court of competent jurisdiction subordinate to him.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (39512)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Power of village courts to impose fine or to award compensation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665&sectionId=39512&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) A village court shall`
  line `record its decision in writing and may sentence an offender convicted by it to pay a fine not exceeding`
  line `two hundred rupees or in default to imprisonment for a term not exceeding one month.`
  line
  line `(2) When a village court imposes a fine under sub-section (1), it may, when passing the order, direct`
  line `that whole or any part of the fine recovered shall be applied in payment of compensation for any loss or`
  line `injury caused by the offence.`
  line
  line `(3) When a person has been sentenced to imprisonment under sub-section (1)`
  line `in default of payment of fine, if such fine be not paid within ten days of the passing of the sentence or within such further time,`
  line `if any, as the village court may allow, the court may cause him to be arrested and may commit him to the`
  line `nearest jail to serve his sentence:`
  line
  line `Provided that notwithstanding anything contained in the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860)—`
  line
  line `(a) the fine imposed by a village court shall not be realised from any person who has served his`
  line `term of imprisonment under this section;`
  line
  line `(b) the person serving his term of imprisonment shall be forthwith released, if the fine is paid`
  line `before the expiry of the term of imprisonment:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no woman shall be sentenced to imprisonment in default of payment of fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (39513)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Power of village to release certain offenders after admonition or on probation of good conduct.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665&sectionId=39513&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `When any person is convicted by a village court of an offence punishable under section`
  line `26 and no previous conviction is proved against him, if it appears to the said court, regard being had to`
  line `the age, character and antecedents of the offender and the circumstances in which the offence was`
  line `committed, that it is expedient—`
  line
  line `(a) that the offender should be released after due admonition, the village court may instead of`
  line `sentencing him to any punishment, release him after due admonition; or`
  line
  line `(b) that the offender should be released on probation of good conduct, the village court may,`
  line `notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898), instead of`
  line `sentencing him at once to any punishment, direct that he be released on his executing a bond for a`
  line `sum not exceeding two hundred rupees to appear and receive sentence when called upon during such`
  line `period not exceeding one year as the village court may direct, and in the meantime to keep the peace`
  line `and be of good behaviour.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (39514)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Power of village courts to permit compounding of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665&sectionId=39514&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898), the village court may allow the parties to`
  line `compound any offence tried by it.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (39515)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Power to transfer criminal cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665&sectionId=39515&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `The Deputy Commissioner or the sub-divisional magistrate,`
  line `either on application made to him in this behalf, or on his own motion, may transfer any case from one`
  line `village court to another or to any other court subordinate to him.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (39516)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Jurisdiction of village courts in civil cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665&sectionId=39516&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code`
  line `of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), or in any other law for the time being in force, but subject to the`
  line `provisions of section 31 and section 32, the village court and the ordinary civil court, within the local`
  line `limits of whose jurisdiction the village is situated, shall have concurrent jurisdiction to try the following`
  line `classes of suits, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) suits for money due on contracts;`
  line
  line `(b) suits for the recovery of movable property or the value of such property;`
  line
  line `(c) suits for compensation for wrongfully taking or injuring movable property; and`
  line
  line `(d) suits for damages by cattle trespass;`
  line
  line `when the value of the suit does not exceed five hundred rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (39517)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Certain suits not to be tried by village courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665&sectionId=39517&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `No suit shall lie in any village court—`
  line
  line `(a) on a balance of partnership account,`
  line
  line `(b) for a share or part of a share under an intestacy of for a legacy or part of a legacy under`
  line `a will,`
  line
  line `(c) by or against the Government or public officers in their official capacity,`
  line
  line `(d) by or against minors or persons of unsound mind.`
  line
  line `(e) for the assessment, enhancement, reduction, abetment, apportionment, or recovery of rent of`
  line `immovable property.`
  line
  line `(f) for recovery of immovable property, or`
  line
  line `(g) for enforcement or redemption of a mortgage of immovable property.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (39518)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Local limits of jurisdiction of village courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665&sectionId=39518&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `No suit shall lie in any village court, unless at`
  line `least one of the defendants resides within the local limits of its jurisdiction at the time of the institution of`
  line `the suit, and the cause of action has arisen wholly or in part within those limits.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (39519)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `How suits may be instituted.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665&sectionId=39519&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) A suit before a village court may be instituted by a petition`
  line `made orally or in writing, and if the petition, is made orally, the court shall record such particulars as may`
  line `be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The plaintiff on instituting his suit shall state the value of the claim.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (39520)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Suits barred by limitation are not triable by village courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665&sectionId=39520&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) If at any time the village`
  line `court is of opinion that the suit is barred by limitation, the court shall, by order in writing, dismiss the`
  line suits.
  line
  line `(2) If at any time it appears to the village court that it has no jurisdiction to entertain the suit, the court`
  line `shall direct the plaintiff to the proper court.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (39521)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Dismissal of suits for default.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665&sectionId=39521&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `If in any suit before a village court the plaintiff fails to appear on`
  line `the date fixed or if in the opinion of the court he shows negligence in prosecuting his suit, the court may`
  line `dismiss the suit for default:`
  line
  line `Provided that a village court may restore a suit dismissed for default, if within thirty days from the`
  line `date of such dismissal the plaintiff satisfies the court that he was prevented by sufficient cause from`
  line `appearing on the date fixed.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (39522)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Summons to defendants to appear and answer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665&sectionId=39522&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `If on receiving the petition the village court is`
  line `satisfied that the trial of the suit may be proceeded with, it shall by summons or otherwise require the`
  line `defendant to appear and answer orally or in writing the claim made in the suit.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (39545)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Ex parte decision.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665&sectionId=39545&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `If the defendant fails to appear and the village court is satisfied that he has`
  line `received notice of the date fixed for hearing, the court may decide the suit ex parte:`
  line
  line `Provided that any defendant against whom a suit has been decided ex parte may, within thirty days`
  line `from the date of executing any processes for enforcement of the decision, apply orally or in writing, to the`
  line `village court to set aside the order; and the court, if satisfied, that the defendant did not receive due notice`
  line `of the date of hearing or was prevented by any sufficient cause from appearing on the date fixed, shall set`
  line `aside the decision and shall appoint a day for proceeding with the suit.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (39546)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `No order to be set aside without notice to opposite party.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665&sectionId=39546&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `No decision or order or a village`
  line `court shall be set aside under section 35 or section 37 unless notice in writing has been served by the`
  line `village court on the opposite party in the prescribed manner.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (39524)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Power of village courts to determine necessary parties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665&sectionId=39524&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of`
  line `clause (c) or clause (d) of section 31 the village court may add as parties to a suit any persons whose`
  line `presence as parties it considers necessary for the proper decision thereof, and shall enter the names of`
  line `such parties in the register of suits, and the suit shall be tried as between the parties whose names are`
  line `entered in the said register:`
  line
  line `Provided that when any party is added, notice shall be given to him and he shall be given an`
  line `opportunity of appearing before the trial of the suit is proceeded with.`
  line
  line `(2) In all cases where a new party appears under the proviso to sub-section (1) during the trial of a`
  line `suit, he may require that the trial shall begin de novo.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (39525)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Certain suits not to be tried by village courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665&sectionId=39525&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `No village court shall proceed with the trial of`
  line `any suit in which the matter directly and substantially in dispute is pending for decision in the same`
  line `court or in any other court in a previously instituted suit between the same parties or between parties`
  line `under whom they or any of them claim, or has been heard and finally decided in a suit between the same`
  line `parties, or between parties under whom they or any of them claim.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (39526)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Decision of village courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665&sectionId=39526&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `When the parties or their agents have been heard and the evidence`
  line `on both sides considered, the village court shall, by written order, pass such decree as may seem just,`
  line `equitable and according to good conscience, stating in the decree the amounts payable as fees under`
  line `section 45, and the amount, if any, paid to witnesses under section 51 and the persons by whom such`
  line `amounts are payable.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (39527)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title Instalments.
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665&sectionId=39527&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `A village court in ordering the payment of a sum of money or the delivery of any`
  line `movable property may direct that the money be paid or the movable property be delivered, by instalments.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (39528)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Decision of village court to be final; but power to order retrial.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665&sectionId=39528&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `The decision of a village`
  line `court in any suit shall be final as between the parties to the suits:`
  line
  line `Provided that the district judge may on application of any party to the suit made within thirty days`
  line `from the date of the decree of the village court, cancel or modify the decree or order of the village court or`
  line `direct a retrial of the suit by the same or any other village court or by any other court subordinate to him if`
  line `he is satisfied that there has been a failure of justice.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (39529)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Death of parties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665&sectionId=39529&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `If the plaintiff or defendant in any suit dies before the suit has been decided,`
  line `the suit may, subject to the provisions of clause (d) of section 31, be proceeded with at the instance of or`
  line `against the legal representatives of the deceased plaintiff or defendant, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (39530)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title Fees.
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665&sectionId=39530&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `(1) In all suits instituted in a village court a fee of one anna in the rupee shall be payable`
  line `in advance by the plaintiff on the amount of the claim upto fifty rupees, and of half anna for every rupee`
  line `of the claim above fifty rupees, and such fees shall not be paid to either party.`
  line
  line `(2) If the claim in the suit is decreed in full, the amount equal to the fee shall be realised from the`
  line `judgement-debtor together with the amount decreed.`
  line
  line `(3) If the claim in a suit is decreed in part, an amount equal to a proportionate part of the fee shall be`
  line `realised from the judgement-debtor together with the amount decreed.`
  line
  line `(4) Any amount realised under sub-section (2) or sub-section (3) shall be paid to the decree-holder.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (39531)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Execution of decree.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665&sectionId=39531&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the village court passing a decree is unable to effect satisfaction`
  line `thereof, it shall grant the decree-holder a certificate to that effect stating the amount due to him on`
  line `account of the decree and the amount due on account of fees under section 45.`
  line
  line `(2) Any decree-holder wishing to execute a decree of a village court may apply to the court of the`
  line `munsiff within the local limits of whose jurisdiction the village is situated and shall present with his`
  line `application a certified copy of the decree of the village court; but no application for execution shall be`
  line `entertained by the court of the munsiff,—`
  line
  line `(a) unless the village court has certified that it is a unable to effect satisfaction of the decree, and`
  line
  line `(b) unless the application is made after the expiry of three months from the date of the decree.`
  line
  line `(3) In executing a decree of the village court the court of the munsiff shall have the same powers and`
  line `shall follow the same procedure as if it were executing a decree passed by itself.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (39532)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Limitation for execution of decree or order.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665&sectionId=39532&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `An application for execution of a decree of a`
  line `village court made after the expiry of three years from the date of the decree or of any order under`
  line `section 43 modifying any such decree, shall be dismissed, although limitation has not been pleaded:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the application is made for execution of a decree or order to enforce payment of`
  line `a sum of money or delivery of any movable property which the decree or order directs to be made at a`
  line `certain date, the application may be made within three years from that date.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (39533)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Procedure before village courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665&sectionId=39533&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `(1) The provisions of—`
  line
  line `(a) the Court Fees Act, 1870 (7 of 1870),`
  line
  line `(b) the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898), and`
  line
  line `(c) the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908),`
  line
  line `shall not apply to any trial or any criminal case or civil suit before a village court.`
  line
  line `(2) The procedure to be followed by a village court in any criminal case or civil suit and in the`
  line `enforcement of its decisions, sentences, decrees and orders, and in the method of forming a quorum shall`
  line `be prescribed by rules made under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The Indian Evidence Act, 1872 (1 of 1872) shall not apply in the trial of any case or suit by a`
  line `village court but the village court shall observe as far as possible the principles underlying that Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (39534)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Persons who are to preside over village courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665&sectionId=39534&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `(1) The village court shall be presided over by`
  line `the chairman of the Village Authority if he is a member of the court.`
  line
  line `(2) If the chairman of the Village Authority is absent from a sitting of the village suit of if he is not a`
  line `member of the court shall elect its own President.`
  line
  line `(3) In the case of difference of opinion among the members of the court the opinion of the majority`
  line `shall prevail and the decisions and orders of the court shall be expressed in terms of the views of the`
  line majority.
  line
  line `(4) In the case of an equality of votes the person presiding over the court shall have a second or`
  line `casting vote.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (39547)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Village courts not to try any case or suiting in which the Village authority or any member thereof is interested.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665&sectionId=39547&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `No village court shall try any criminal case or any civil suit to or in which the`
  line `Village Authority or any member thereof is a party or is interested.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (39536)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Attendance of witnesses.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665&sectionId=39536&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of section 53 a village court may by`
  line `summons or otherwise send for any person to appear and give evidence or to produce or cause the`
  line `production of any document.`
  line
  line `(2) A village court shall refuse to summon a witness or to enforce a summons already issued against a`
  line `witness, where in the opinion of the court the attendance of the witness cannot be procured without an`
  line `amount of delay, expense, or inconvenience which under the circumstances of the case would be`
  line unreasonable.
  line
  line `(3) A village court shall not require any person living at a distance of five miles or more from the seat`
  line `of the village court to give evidence or produce any document unless such sum of money be paid to him`
  line `as appears to the court to be sufficient to defray his travelling and other expenses in passing to and from`
  line `the court and for one day's attendance.`
  line
  line `(4) If any person whom a village court summons by written order to appear or give evidence or to`
  line `produce any document before it, fails to obey such summons, such person shall be guilty of an offence`
  line `and the village court may take cognizance of such offence and may sentence any person convicted thereof`
  line `to a fine not exceeding twenty-five rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (39537)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `Appearance of parties before village courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665&sectionId=39537&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `(1) The parties to criminal cases triable by a`
  line `village court shall appear personally before the court:`
  line
  line `Provided that the village court, if it sees reason so to do, may dispense with the personal attendance of`
  line `the accused and permit him to appear by agent.`
  line
  line `(2) The parties to civil suits triable by a village court may appear by agent.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—In sub-section (1) and sub-section (2), "agent" means a full-time servant or a partner or`
  line `a relative of the party whom the village court may admit as a fit person to represent that party and who is`
  line `authorised to appear and plead for such party.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in any law, legal practitioners shall not be permitted to`
  line `practice before a village court.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (39538)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title `Appearance of women.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665&sectionId=39538&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `No woman shall, against her will, be compelled to appear in person`
  line `before a village court as an accused or as a party or as a witness.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (39539)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Realisation of fees, fines, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665&sectionId=39539&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `All fees and fines imposed, all sums decreed or compensation`
  line `awarded and all sums due on bonds under this Act may be realised under orders of the village court in`
  line `such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (39540)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Registers and records.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665&sectionId=39540&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `Every village court shall maintain registers and records and submit such`
  line `returns as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (39541)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title `Language of village courts.`
  content `All proceedings before a village court shall be Manipuri.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665&sectionId=39541&sectionno=56&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (39542)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 57
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665&sectionId=39542&sectionno=57&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chief Commissioner may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, make rules for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the preparation, revision and final publication of electoral rolls for election of members of a`
  line `Village Authority and the particulars to be entered in such rolls;`
  line
  line `(b) the preliminary publication of electoral rolls in the village to which they relate;`
  line
  line `(c) the manner in which and the time within which claims and objections as to entries in electoral`
  line `rolls may be preferred and the authority by whom such claims and objections may be decided;`
  line
  line `(d) the nomination of candidates, the time and manner of holding elections and the manner in`
  line `which votes shall be given;`
  line
  line `(e) any other matter relating to elections to Village Authorities or election disputes arising`
  line therefrom;
  line
  line `(f) the regulation of the conduct of business of the Village Authorities and the number of`
  line `members necessary to form a quorum;`
  line
  line `(g) the registers and records to be maintained and the returns to be submitted by Village`
  line `Authorities and village courts and the particulars to be entered in such registers, records and returns;`
  line
  line `(h) the procedure to be followed by a village court in the institution, trial and disposal of criminal`
  line `cases and civil suits and the number of members necessary to form a quorum of a village court;`
  line
  line `(i) the issue, service or execution of summons and other processes by village courts and the issue`
  line `and service of notice by village Authorities;`
  line
  line `(j) the procedure for the transfer of criminal cases and civil suits from one village court to another`
  line `village court or to any other court;`
  line
  line `(k) the procedure for the execution of decrees, orders and sentences of village courts;`
  line
  line `(l) the fees to be levied by village courts for copies of documents and the procedure to be`
  line `followed in furnishing such copies; and`
  line
  line `(m) any other mater which has to be or may be prescribed under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (39543)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 58
  title `Repeal and savings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665&sectionId=39543&sectionno=58&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00009_195680_1517807321665
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `The Manipur State Hill Peoples (Administration) Regulation, 1947, in so`
  line `far as it relates to the constitution and functions of village Authorities and the administration of justice,`
  line `both civil and criminal, by courts of village Authorities, is hereby repealed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the said repeal shall not affect—`
  line
  line `(a) the previous operation of the said Regulation, or`
  line
  line `(b) any right, privilege, obligation or liability acquired, accrued or incurred under the said`
  line `Regulation, or`
  line
  line `(c) any penalty, forfeiture or punishment in respect of any offence committed under the said`
  line `Regulation, or`
  line
  line `(d) any investigation, legal proceeding or remedy in respect of any right, privilege, obligation,`
  line `liability, penalty, forfeiture, or punishment as aforesaid,`
  line
  line `and any such investigation, legal proceeding or remedy may be instituted, continued or enforced, and any`
  line `such penalty, forfeiture of punishment may be imposed as if this Act had not been passed:`
  line
  line `Provided further that subject to the above provisions, anything done or any action taken (including`
  line `any appointment or delegation made or any notification, instruction or direction issued or any rule,`
  line `regulation or form made or framed) under the said Regulation shall in so far as such thing or action is not`
  line `inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, continue in force, and be deemed to have been done or taken`
  line `under the corresponding provisions of this Act, unless and until it is superseded by anything done or any`
  line `action taken under the provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
